## ğŸš€ Running .exe Files | è¿è¡Œ .exe æ–‡ä»¶

### English

<details>
<summary><b>Basic Execution</b></summary>

1. **Navigate to directory containing .exe file:**
   ```bash
   cd /path/to/your/file
   ```

2. **Run the .exe file:**
   ```bash
   wine filename.exe
   ```

3. **For GUI applications, you might need:**
   ```bash
   pkg install x11-repo -y
   pkg install termux-x11-nightly -y
   ```
</details>

<details>
<summary><b>Common Commands</b></summary>

- **Check Wine configuration:**
  ```bash
  winecfg
  ```

- **Install Windows DLLs/components:**
  ```bash
  winetricks
  ```

- **Run Windows program installer:**
  ```bash
  wine msiexec /i installer.msi
  ```

- **Create Wine prefix (virtual Windows environment):**
  ```bash
   WINEARCH=win32 WINEPREFIX=~/win32 winecfg
  ```
</details>

### ä¸­æ–‡

<details>
<summary><b>åŸºæœ¬æ‰§è¡Œæ–¹æ³•</b></summary>

1. **å¯¼èˆªåˆ°åŒ…å« .exe æ–‡ä»¶çš„ç›®å½•:**
   ```bash
   cd /path/to/your/file
   ```

2. **è¿è¡Œ .exe æ–‡ä»¶:**
   ```bash
   wine filename.exe
   ```

3. **å¯¹äº GUI åº”ç”¨ç¨‹åºï¼Œå¯èƒ½éœ€è¦:**
   ```bash
