## ğŸ”§ Advanced Usage | é«˜çº§ç”¨æ³•

### English

<details>
<summary><b>Creating Desktop Shortcuts</b></summary>

1. **Create .desktop file:**
   ```bash
   nano ~/.local/share/applications/myapp.desktop
   ```

2. **Add content:**
   ```ini
   [Desktop Entry]
   Name=My Application
   Exec=wine /path/to/app.exe
   Type=Application
   Categories=Utility;
   ```

3. **Make executable:**
   ```bash
   chmod +x ~/.local/share/applications/myapp.desktop
   ```
</details>

<details>
<summary><b>Using Different Wine Versions</b></summary>

1. **Download Wine from Termux repository:**
   ```bash
   pkg install wine -y
   ```

2. **Or compile from source:**
   ```bash
   git clone https://github.com/wine-mirror/wine
   cd wine
   ./configure
   make
   ```
</details>

### ä¸­æ–‡

<details>
<summary><b>åˆ›å»ºæ¡Œé¢å¿«æ·æ–¹å¼</b></summary>

1. **åˆ›å»º .desktop æ–‡ä»¶:**
   ```bash
   nano ~/.local/share/applications/myapp.desktop
   ```

2. **æ·»åŠ å†…å®¹:**
   ```ini
   [Desktop Entry]
   Name=æˆ‘çš„åº”ç”¨ç¨‹åº
   Exec=wine /path/to/app.exe
   Type=Application
   Categories=Utility;
   ```

3. **è®¾ç½®ä¸ºå¯æ‰§è¡Œ:**
   ```bash
   chmod +x ~/.local/share/applications/myapp.desktop
   ```
</details>

<details>
<summary><b>ä½¿ç”¨ä¸åŒ Wine ç‰ˆæœ¬</b></summary>

1. **ä» Termux ä»“åº“ä¸‹è½½ Wine:**
   ```bash
   pkg install wine -y
